MAXR I will be royally piED to see a buyout on this stock The true value on a possible turnaround will be far far greater than any buyout IMO Itll be a situation as once again where shareholders get the shaft Another risk is MAXR issuing shares to reduce debt load which of course would dilute existing shareholders Current debt loads as indicated in the previous quarterly conference were considered optimal for the stock So a stock issue at these levels would be theftfull stop If we have the ability to stay the course then who cares about institutions clamoring on about debt levels I dont think they were clamoring on about debt levels when the stock was at lower revenues and slapping US 60 price targets on the stock CAD 80 Ifwhen institutions are convinced of a turnaround theyll be paying a multiple of current share priceall other things being equal
